The paper presents an algorithm for finding holes in high dimensional data, which is a problem in data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The algorithm is also useful for big data analysis and automated knowledge discovery, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithm's efficiency is also discussed, which is a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
